rComments: Forced to take him as he was the only prof. Might be the worst prof i've had in Telfer, his lectures consisted of him typing into a powerpoint slide and reading what he wrote down. They were boring, uninteresting and his class requires you to make connections to what he says and the textbook itself which has probably been the worst textbook ever.

Emphasized first thing in his lecture about not making friends with students. Asked Bruce about course expectation during break but got turned down for "trying to be friends with him". CUMULATIVE exam, little to no guidance. Avoid this professor, pick Giles Lavasseur to save some brain cells.

I learned more from the textbook than him, his lectures seem to be more rambles than anything. But he is more than willing to answer questions and help you understand if you're really stuck. He's passionate about his politics so you will hear about it more than once. And I think the grading is fair. All in all It definitely wasn't my worst class.
teacherRatingTags: ['Gives good feedback', 'Get ready to read', 'Lecture heavy']

rComments: Great Professor. He is a fair and honest marker. He sends out sample answers from your midterm from your own class, and if you have any problems you can send him an email whenever with comparison to these answers to your own. He relates a lot of what he teaches to real life applications, which enhances learning in my opinion. Enjoyed the semester.

Amazing Prof! Show up to class, pay attention, participate, and read the textbook! Lays out the class expectations so simple. Rants a little, but always interesting to hear! Find a good group for assignments. Fluffing on midterms is your best friend. He will give back as much as you give into his class. Memorize & understand charts in textbook.
teacherRatingTags: ['Accessible outside class', 'Lecture heavy', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: Mind you I had a 3 hour night class with Professor La Rochelle from 7 to 10 PM. He would always kick off his lecture with 30 minutes of useless mumble about politics and other worldly issues. Also despises multiple choice exams. I stopped attending class after the 3rd lecture I believe, reading the book was both more entertaining and interesting.

Horrible. Its almost impossible to take notes of what he says because he mumbles the whole time, and when he actually speaks clear he's usually babbling about Canadian politics (in an accounting class.) Very unapproachable; dry and cold when asked a question about the material. On the bright side he sometimes jokes around. No need to go class.

He is such an inspiration and the topics he covered in class were not only interesting, but engaging, fascinating and striking. The topic of accounting itself is very boring, but he made it very interesting with the subjects. The exams had no surprises as he pretty much gives the questions out in class. Take his class over Pedwell anyday

One of the worst profs I've ever had. Knows his stuff but is hopeless as a teacher. Unorganised, impossible-to-follow lectures, illegible handwriting compounded with insanely long and poor quality readings and poor response to emails.  AVOID!

The Prof is a good educator.  His lectures and exams are based on the textbook, so there are no surprises on the exams.  Very intelligent guy  although he does seem to babble a bit.  The class group assignments were challenging and the grading of them was ambiguous.  Attendance is mandatory or you will get zero for the class assignments.

I agree with a lot of the below comments. Although I did well in his class, it was stressful and very difficult. His grading is quite subjective, he is a difficult marker for group projects. Tests rely heavily on the textbook. He is a truly brilliant man but as previously mentioned is incoherant, often redudant, illegible hand writing...

I agree with the previous bad comments.If only I did those course evaluations now!he should not be teaching!!he is so busy with other priorities,that the students end up suffering in the end,with last minute Sunday classes,last minute tests(that were postponed from Nov5 eachweek to finally..the week of exams) this is absolutely notfair for students

Terrible prof for any fundamental accounting course. I hear he is good for business law, but his teaching methods are useless for any fundamental course. Switch out of his course. Disrespectful to students, no help,

Extremely knowledgeable professor.  Responded quickly to emails and was willing to help.  Does not provide much feedback and marking seemed a bit ambiguous.  However overall a great professor and made a boring class interesting.

Very good professor.  Extremely knowledgable in many areas, and conveys the subject matter effectively.  If you go to class and listen you should have no problem doing well.  The exams and assignments were very fair, and he was always available and very willing to address any questions.

This professor is very knowledgeable and I definately find that he delivers most of the material in an effective manner. Most of the stuff he tests you on is relevant and he expects you to understand the material and not just memorize formulas. He values academic honesty and overall is a pretty good Prof!

He is a great prof for law imo...he does know his stuff and his expectations are very straightforward for that class...discuss the legal issues.. if you read the book or just pay attention in class it should be easy...he tries to help his students as much as his can but he is too busy and gets stuff back really late but overall its a decent course
Good Prof,I really like him@!~

Interesting prof. Is a practicing lawyer, CA, CMA, MBA, AND a PhD in Organizational Behaviour. Terrible hand writing and mumbles a lot. But knows his stuff and is actually a funny guy if you get to know him. Not sure if he's an effective teacher. Always likes to bring canadian politics into lectures which can be interesting but usually not.

At first I heard about unfavorable comments about this prof. True, his writing is terrible and he mumbles. But if you sit in the front and pay attention, he's very funny and knowledgeable. He cares about his students (not all profs do).

The most amazing prof. I have ever had, I had no previous knowledge of business or law and I got an A+ in his class. Listen to him in class, and take the notes that he writes(its better to sit at the front). He expects students to put an effort in the assignments even if they are worth only 5%.
His teaching style seems terrible, and the lowest midterm Avg I heard. Dont take his courses if it s not necessary.

Business Law. Mumbles a lot, illegible writing, no class notes.  Seems unprepared for class.  Very vague in descriptions, lectures, and assignments.  Has extremely high expectations from undergrads. Expects students to have some high level knowledge of the course. Knows what he's talking about though.
Took his class 3 years ago.  He was an excellent professor and I believe he's still does.  He has a sense of humor but you have to dig it out.

Expects Masters level work in undergrad class.  Assignments (ambiguous at best) worth 1.5% require 5 page research paper to pass (avg. marks are fails).  If taking class with this prof expect lots of theoretical essays, hard marking with minimal guidance.  Must get on his good side to pass!!

His hand writing is horrible but he's still not willing to provide notes on the web sites. Assignment&mid-term are all long essay questions. Very low class average for the assignments&mid-term (final not sure yet). Feels like he wants to make an easy course as tough as possible..
Excellent prof... Easy to listen to.  Class is never boring.  He's got like a million degrees and he know's what he's talking about.  Don't get on his bad side and you'll do fine.
No Comments
Apparently the class' avg for his midterm is 42%. Enough said. I was given no choice but to take his class this summer, so...Lord help me :(
